Completion (such as specification) network
(of useful specific structures like specific values that are frequently useful, like being useful to connect)

div.div:
Incomplete (such as abstract) interface structure network
(of useful specific structures like 'lists of indexes/definitions/requirements' such as 'sequences of problem types/intents' that are likely useful to connect).
This can be a problem type/problem-solving intent network, a set of specific index/definition/requirement/interface structures that are connected in some sequence like 'frequency/cause sequences', a standardized similarity network, a relevant variation of relevant graph network, a graph of useful graphs, or some other network that acts like a useful 'abstract template to fill in with specifications' or otherwise applies an interface spectrum in a useful way. Other networks can apply other interface spectrums to connect networks to fulfill problem-solving intents (specify an abstraction being a problem-solving intent).
